  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3205",
  "title": "There is no way to display the search query in currentRefinedValues while `onlyListedAttributes: true`",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\nThe search query is not shown in the *currentRefinedValues* widget when `onlyListedAttributes` is set to true.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Go to https://codesandbox.io/s/8y2jrkz8o9\r\n2. Filter by brand and see the brand is shown in the *currentRefinedValues* widget.\r\n3. Enter a custom search query\r\n4. See error, the search query is not displayed in the *currentRefinedValues* widget.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\nThe search query should show up in the *currentRefinedValues* widget even when whitelisting the other shown attributes with `onlyListedAttributes: true`. If not by default, we should have a way of enabling it.\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @stianmartinsen in https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/pull/2414#issuecomment-430514274_",
